Dialysis Centers
The Sterilis System is Designed to Provide the Best Regulated Medical Waste Services Required by the Most Demanding Dialysis Centers:

The system can effectively and efficiently transform dialyzers, tubing, gauze, rubber gloves, glass ampules, sharps, and all other forms of regulated medical waste into sterile regular trash. 
The 7 gallon vessel can handle a minimum of 5 dialyzers and associated tubing per process 
If you are spending more than $700/month in regulated medical waste hauling costs the Sterilis system provides immediate savings.
One-year manufacturer’s warranty included.
The machine has a small footprint of 36”W x 24”D x 47”H and requires no fixed plumbing or fixtures only 110V plug. 
The size and convenience allows you the opportunity to position the machine in a location outside the view of patients yet close to where the waste is generated which reduces the handling and storage of infectious waste.
Processing sounds are equal to regular conversation level (60 decibels) resulting in no distractions for patient care and office settings.
Easy to use contemporary touch screen allows employees to simply and safely place the waste into the system, press a button and the system does the rest. 
Internal WiFi allows you to store regulatory data electronically and eliminates time consuming manual record keeping.
24 hour service and customer support. 
Transforming regulated medical waste into sterile solid waste helps protect our environment.



The Sterilis System provides ease of use, safety, convenience and cost savings features in one remarkable device!
Please contact us for more information on the features and benefits of Sterilis, LLC.

